Ada Wodu, Calabar The Cross River State Local Government Service Commission, has started the training of 200 civil servants in the Boki Local Government Area in records and information management, information security, and preparation of financial records, among others. The exercise, which is being replicated in the other 17 councils of the state, was declared open in Boki by the Supervisory Commissioner for Boki, Darlington Eyo, who represented the commission’s Chairman, Dr Peter Adigeb. Adigeb said staff training and retraining was an inherent mandate of the Local Government Service Commission and commended the Governor Ayade-led administration for creating the enabling environment for the training to commence. Copyright PUNCH.
